<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1366,1537]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
Comments: According to the original description and the information on the label, the 
<typeStatus box="[1120,1223,1366,1392]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">lectotype</typeStatus>
specimen was collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[256,369,1402,1428]" name="Colombia" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, but this species has never been recorded in northern South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Velez, D. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[1162,1425,1402,1428]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="46 - 63" refId="ref20881" refString="Velez, D. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2018) Sinopsis de las especies del subgenero Centris (Ptilotopus) (Hymenoptera: Apidae) en Colombia. Biota Colombiana, 19 (2), 46 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.21068 / c 2018. v 19 n 02 a 05" type="journal article" year="2018">VÃ©lez &amp; Vivallo, 2018</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[151,320,1439,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sponsa">
<emphasis box="[151,320,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Centris sponsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in northeastern and southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[781,849,1438,1464]" name="Brazil" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Silveira, F. A. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Almeida, E. A. B." box="[865,1093,1438,1465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" refId="ref19793" refString="Silveira, F. A., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Almeida, E. A. B. (2002) Abelhas brasileiras Sistematica e Identificacao. Fundacao Araucaria, Belo Horizonte, 254 pp." type="book" year="2002">
Silveira 
<emphasis box="[961,1011,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">et al</emphasis>
., 2002
</bibRefCitation>
), so is very likely that the 
<typeStatus pageId="19" pageNumber="170">lectotype</typeStatus>
was mislabeled (as well as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[574,742,1474,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculifrons">
<emphasis box="[574,593,1475,1501]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[609,742,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">maculifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see above) thus incorrectly recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[1210,1324,1474,1500]" name="Colombia" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. The type locality cannot be further narrowed down than to 
<collectingCountry box="[706,820,1510,1536]" name="Colombia" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
